Here's a look at WR 40 yard dash times vs their career receiving EPA.

Moral of the story: Being average might not be so bad. Few sub-4.3 guys even met the target minimum for this chart, but >4.6 is not good either. Most of the elite WRs are between 4.35 and 4.55

Data: #nflverse https://t.co/ZBbQOYFc6x

An upcoming update for nflreadr will include a #nflverse print method that will show the timestamp of nflverse data. 
Tan is teasing it here. https://t.co/vdD64HCLSM
